23/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Attending the multinational military exercise Co-operative Engagement 2005 in Vlora on Thursday (22 September), Prime Minister Sali Berisha stressed that he, the government and the army are determined to make every effort to achieve the goal of Albanian membership in NATO. He added that he believes Albania will find its own place in the Alliance, and stressed the government would work intensively on reform of land, sea and air forces to prepare them for compatibility with NATO standards. Commanders of the exercise praised the level of preparedness demonstrated by the Albanian naval officers.
In other news Thursday, Berisha met with Turkish Minister of Culture and Tourism Atilla Koc in Tirana. They discussed ways to extend co-operation and agreed to establish joint commissions on cultural and tourist relations. (Albanian News - 23/09/05)
